    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the substance of this conversation has been found. The fact
                    that <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName> had an appointment with
                        <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> on November 23 is indicated
                    in a letter from <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName>’s aide (Major
                        <persName corresp="#p_HJ2">John Henry</persName>) to <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName>, dated November 23, 1943 (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers).</p>
                <p>In an interview with one of the editors in 1956, <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1"
                        >Hurley</persName> recalled the time and place of the meeting as indicated
                    above. He stated that Madame <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> was
                    present at the meeting. According to <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1"
                        >Hurley</persName>’s recollection, <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1"
                        >Chiang</persName> asked whether <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>
                    were to meet with <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>, to which
                        <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName> replied that such a meeting
                    was scheduled but not for Cairo. <persName corresp="#p_HPJ1">Hurley</persName>
                    also recalled discussing with <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1">Chiang</persName> the
                    pending plan for American-British-Chinese military cooperation in Burma.
                    (110.4–HD/12–1756.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
